[
    {
        "content": "<p>I can't understand the def of compactness in mathlib. Can anyone give a short proof of the equivalence between this and the usual \"finite covering\" def?<br>\n\"A set s is compact if for every nontrivial filter f that contains s, there exists a ∈ s such that every set of f meets every neighborhood of a.\"</p>",
        "id": 292321934,
        "sender_full_name": "Jiatong Yang",
        "timestamp": 1659881583
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The equivalence is <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/is_compact_iff_finite_subcover\">docs#is_compact_iff_finite_subcover</a>.</p>",
        "id": 292322412,
        "sender_full_name": "Junyan Xu",
        "timestamp": 1659882182
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm sorry. Is there a more mathematical proof? <span aria-label=\"rolling on the floor laughing\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f923\" role=\"img\" title=\"rolling on the floor laughing\">:rolling_on_the_floor_laughing:</span></p>",
        "id": 292323296,
        "sender_full_name": "Jiatong Yang",
        "timestamp": 1659883332
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Jiatong, the docstring you quote is confusing because it breaks the abstraction barrier of the implementation of filters in \"that contains s\". It would be much better to say that <code>f</code> as a generalized set is contained in <code>s</code>, and this is indeed much closer to how the actual definition is stated.</p>",
        "id": 292323303,
        "sender_full_name": "Patrick Massot",
        "timestamp": 1659883340
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I can now use filter to describe some limit procedures, but when I am given a filter, I don't know what to do to use it.</p>",
        "id": 292323911,
        "sender_full_name": "Jiatong Yang",
        "timestamp": 1659884227
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe watching <a href=\"https://icerm.brown.edu/video_archive/?play=2899\">https://icerm.brown.edu/video_archive/?play=2899</a> could help</p>",
        "id": 292323971,
        "sender_full_name": "Patrick Massot",
        "timestamp": 1659884326
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"478392\">@Jiatong Yang</span> setting up topology using filters is a really cool trick but if you don't want a filter then you probably never need to deal with them. Just because the internal implementation of something uses filters this doesn't matter to an end user, who can just use the API (ie the theorems).</p>",
        "id": 292328527,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1659890928
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe it helps to think about what the statement looks like when applied to the whole space. In the topology library we like to make definitions about sets, but it is often harder to parse. Here, this really just means \"a topological space <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> is compact iff each nontrivial filter on <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> has a cluster point\" (<a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/cluster_pt\">docs#cluster_pt</a>)</p>",
        "id": 292333070,
        "sender_full_name": "Anatole Dedecker",
        "timestamp": 1659897280
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Here is a mathematical proof. We'll use the dual characterization of compactness (with intersections of closed sets), and the fact that cluster points of a filter <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">F</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathcal{F}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.09931em;\">F</span></span></span></span> are exactly the elements of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mo>⋂</mo><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">F</mi></mrow></msub><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>A</mi><mo>ˉ</mo></mover></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\bigcap_{A\\in\\mathcal{F}}\\bar{A}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.1472em;vertical-align:-0.3271em;\"></span><span class=\"mop\"><span class=\"mop op-symbol small-op\" style=\"position:relative;top:0em;\">⋂</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1786em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.4003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">A</span><span class=\"mrel mtight\">∈</span><span class=\"mord mathcal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.09931em;\">F</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3271em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord accent\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8201em;\"><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span></span><span style=\"top:-3.2523em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"accent-body\" style=\"left:-0.1111em;\"><span class=\"mord\">ˉ</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>First, assume <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> is compact, and let <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">F</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathcal{F}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.09931em;\">F</span></span></span></span> be a nontrivial filter on <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span>. By contradiction, assume that <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">F</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathcal{F}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.09931em;\">F</span></span></span></span> has no cluster point, i.e <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mo>⋂</mo><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">F</mi></mrow></msub><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>A</mi><mo>ˉ</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∅</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\bigcap_{A\\in\\mathcal{F}}\\bar{A} = \\varnothing</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.1472em;vertical-align:-0.3271em;\"></span><span class=\"mop\"><span class=\"mop op-symbol small-op\" style=\"position:relative;top:0em;\">⋂</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1786em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.4003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">A</span><span class=\"mrel mtight\">∈</span><span class=\"mord mathcal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.09931em;\">F</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3271em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord accent\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8201em;\"><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span></span><span style=\"top:-3.2523em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"accent-body\" style=\"left:-0.1111em;\"><span class=\"mord\">ˉ</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6633em;vertical-align:-0.0817em;\"></span><span class=\"mord amsrm\">∅</span></span></span></span>. Since <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> is compact, that gives a finite set <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>J</mi><mo>⊆</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">F</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">J \\subseteq\\mathcal{F}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8193em;vertical-align:-0.136em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.09618em;\">J</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">⊆</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.09931em;\">F</span></span></span></span> with <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mo>⋂</mo><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi>J</mi></mrow></msub><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>A</mi><mo>ˉ</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∅</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\bigcap_{A\\in J}\\bar{A} = \\varnothing</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.1472em;vertical-align:-0.3271em;\"></span><span class=\"mop\"><span class=\"mop op-symbol small-op\" style=\"position:relative;top:0em;\">⋂</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1786em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.4003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">A</span><span class=\"mrel mtight\">∈</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.09618em;\">J</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3271em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord accent\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8201em;\"><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span></span><span style=\"top:-3.2523em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"accent-body\" style=\"left:-0.1111em;\"><span class=\"mord\">ˉ</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6633em;vertical-align:-0.0817em;\"></span><span class=\"mord amsrm\">∅</span></span></span></span> hence <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∅</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mo>⋂</mo><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi>J</mi></mrow></msub><mi>A</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">F</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\varnothing=\\bigcap_{A\\in J} A\\in\\mathcal{F}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6633em;vertical-align:-0.0817em;\"></span><span class=\"mord amsrm\">∅</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0771em;vertical-align:-0.3271em;\"></span><span class=\"mop\"><span class=\"mop op-symbol small-op\" style=\"position:relative;top:0em;\">⋂</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1786em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.4003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">A</span><span class=\"mrel mtight\">∈</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.09618em;\">J</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3271em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"msp